{"description": "By default, the SELinux boolean <tt>fips_mode</tt> is enabled.\nThis allows all SELinux domains to execute in <tt>fips_mode</tt>.\nIf this setting is disabled, it should be enabled.\n\nTo enable the <code>fips_mode</code> SELinux boolean, run the following command:\n<pre>$ sudo setsebool -P fips_mode on</pre>", "rationale": "", "severity": "medium", "references": {"cis-csc": ["13"], "cobit5": ["APO01.06", "DSS05.04", "DSS05.07", "DSS06.02"], "cui": ["3.13.11"], "isa-62443-2013": ["SR 5.2"], "iso27001-2013": ["A.10.1.1", "A.11.1.4", "A.11.1.5", "A.11.2.1", "A.13.1.1", "A.13.1.3", "A.13.2.1", "A.13.2.3", "A.13.2.4", "A.14.1.2", "A.14.1.3", "A.6.1.2", "A.7.1.1", "A.7.1.2", "A.7.3.1", "A.8.2.2", "A.8.2.3", "A.9.1.1", "A.9.1.2", "A.9.2.3", "A.9.4.1", "A.9.4.4", "A.9.4.5"], "nist": ["SC-12(2)", "SC-12(3)", "IA-7", "SC-13", "CM-6(a)", "SC-12"], "nist-csf": ["PR.DS-5"]}, "control_references": {}, "components": ["fips", "selinux"], "identifiers": {}, "ocil_clause": "fips_mode is not enabled", "ocil": "\nRun the following command to determine if the <code>fips_mode</code> SELinux boolean is enabled:\n<pre>$ getsebool fips_mode</pre>\nIf properly configured, the output should show the following:\n<code>fips_mode --> on</code>", "oval_external_content": null, "fixtext": "", "checktext": "", "vuldiscussion": "", "srg_requirement": "", "warnings": [], "conflicts": [], "requires": [], "policy_specific_content": {}, "platform": null, "platforms": [], "sce_metadata": {"check-import": "stdout", "check-export": ["var_fips_mode=xccdf_org.ssgproject.content_value_var_fips_mode"], "platform": ["multi_platform_all"], "environment": "any", "filename": "sebool_fips_mode.sh", "relative_path": "rhel9/checks/sce/sebool_fips_mode.sh"}, "inherited_platforms": ["system_with_kernel", "selinux or bootc or osbuild"], "cpe_platform_names": [], "inherited_cpe_platform_names": ["bootc_or_osbuild_or_selinux", "system_with_kernel"], "bash_conditional": null, "fixes": {}, "check_type": nu